# ============================================================
# جوب البلاد - Environment & Configuration Guide
# ============================================================
#
# This is a purely static frontend app (no server-side code).
# There are NO environment variables to set on Vercel.
#
# Credentials are embedded directly in the source file:
#   api/supabase.js
#
# Edit that file and replace the two placeholder values below.
# ============================================================

# In api/supabase.js, replace:
#
# SUPABASE_URL  = 'YOUR_SUPABASE_PROJECT_URL'
#   → your Supabase project URL, e.g. https://xyz.supabase.co
#
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = 'YOUR_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY'
#   → your project anon/public API key (safe to expose in front-end code)
#
# Both values are found in your Supabase project dashboard:
#   Project Settings → API → Project URL / Project API Keys

# ============================================================
# Google OAuth (for customer sign-in)
# ============================================================
#
# In Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → Google:
#   1. Enable Google provider
#   2. Add Client ID & Client Secret from Google Cloud Console
#   3. Add Authorized Redirect URI:
#      https://<your-vercel-domain>/index.html
#      (or http://localhost:5500/index.html for local dev)

# ============================================================
# Admin account setup
# ============================================================
#
# After deploying, manually promote a user to admin:
#   1. Sign in to your Supabase project
#   2. Go to Table Editor → users
#   3. Find your admin user row
#   4. Set the `role` column to: admin
